bFixed issue with mystery null pointer; figured game plan for tomorrow.

Hannah make sure you use Assert*() as assert*(expected actual). In a
lot of the tests I see you write they are assert*(actual expected).
The reason we had null pointers was because AssertEquals(ab) I guess
is just a masked AssertTrue(a.equals(b)). This combined with forgetting
that since we are working with lots of static stuff means that things
carry over from test to test without a setup method means that ticket 1
was still deleted from a previous test. the ticket you added in the
nullPointer method was actually ticket 3.

I've realized now that the issue with my ticket-based methods is that by
default Ticket objects don't have a notesList. this makes adding things
to it without accounting for that fact incredibly difficult. Luckily
they can be added in by calling another method in the xml package. I'm
going to investigate to see if they just have a method for it in the
jar however.""""Fixed issue with mystery null pointer; figured game plan for tomorrow.
